{
  "texts": [
    "22 Sometimes, the concepts of risk and uncertainty are kept separate, the former being considered calculable and the latter not.",
    "For this purpose, the distinction between epistemic and aleatory uncertainty may be relevant, with only the latter being effectively addressable through risk assessment.",
    "On this, see Renn O.",
    "Risk governance: coping with uncertainty in a complex world.",
    "London: Routledge 2011; 368."
  ]
}